\id JUD - The Orthodox Jewish Bible 
\h LETTER FROM YEHUDA TO THE KEHILLAH 
\toc1 Moshiachʼs Letter through Yehuda, the Brother of the shliach Ya'akov, to the Brit Chadasha Kehillah 
\toc2 Yehuda 
\toc3 Yd 
\mt1 Moshiachʼs Letter through Yehuda, the Brother of the shliach Ya'akov, to the Brit Chadasha Kehillah 
\is1 Introduction 
\ip Notice that this man Yehuda, a direct descendant of King Dovid as well as a brother of one of the Shluchim and a half-brother of Moshiach, is in a position to know what Moshiach Yehoshua taught about the Eish of Gehinnom, mentioned in verse \xt 7\xt* as Eish Olam (eternal fire) and alluded to again in verse \xt 22\xt*. Yehuda is mentioned in \xt Mt 13:55\xt* and was a leader in the early Kehillah whose letter has been treasured from earliest times. Yehuda is one of the iggrot kodesh of the Masores HaZekenim of the Adat Bnei Yisroel of the Derech \nd Hashem\nd*, the authentic Judaism whose objective body of torah all Moshiachʼs Shluchim submitted to in Jerusalem, including the Shliach to the Nations, Rav Sha'ul. 
\c 1  
\p  
\v 1 From Yehuda, eved \add (servant)\add* of Rebbe, Melech HaMoshiach Yehoshua/Yeshua and brother of Ya'akov;\f + \fr 1:1 \ft See \xt Mt 13:55\f* To HaKeru'im \add (the Called Ones)\add*, beloved in Elokim HaAv and HaShemurim \add (the Guarded ones)\add* for Rebbe, Melech HaMoshiach Yehoshua. 
\p  
\v 2 Rachamim \nd Hashem\nd* and Shalom \nd Hashem\nd* and Ahavas \nd Hashem\nd* to you abundantly! 
\p  
\v 3 Chaverim, although I was very eager to write to you an iggeret hakodesh concerning the Geulah \add (Redemption)\add* we share, it suddenly became necessary to write you an urgent appeal to fight for the\f + \fr 1:3 \ft correct Orthodox Jewish\f* Emunah \add (Faith, the Emunah of the true Dat HaYehudit)\add*, which was once for all time handed over and transmitted to the Kedoshim.  
\v 4 For certain men, anshei resha \add (men of wickedness)\add*, written down long ago\f + \fr 1:4 \ft in the sfarim of \+nd Hashem\+nd*\f* for this harsha'ah \add (condemnation)\add*,\f + \fr 1:4 \ft \xt Dan 7:10; Rv 20:12; 1K 2:8\f* have infiltrated our ranks, men twisting the Chen v'Chesed HaElokeinu into a license for sensual self-indulgence and denying our only Ribboneinu and Adoneinu Rebbe, Melech HaMoshiach Yehoshua. 
\p  
\v 5 Now I wish to remind you, though you are fully informed, that \nd Hashem\nd*, Who once saved a people from Eretz Mitzrayim \add (Egypt)\add*, afterwards destroyed every Apikoros not having Emunah \add (Faith)\add*.  
\v 6 And you have da'as about the malachim \add (angels)\add*, not being content to keep their positions of Memshalah \add (Rule, Dominion)\add*, having deserted their own station, these malachim \nd Hashem\nd* has kept under sharsherot \add (chains)\add* oif eibik \add (forever)\add*, under choshech\f + \fr 1:6 \ft See \xt 2K 2:4\f* for the Mishpat HaYom HaGadol, the Judgment of the Great Day.\f + \fr 1:6 \ft the Yom HaDin\f* 
\v 7 As S'dom and Amora and the cities around them, in a doime \add (similar)\add* manner to these, indulging in gilui arayot \add (sexual immorality)\add* against the course of nature and turning aside and going after alien flesh, are set forth to lie in public view as a mofet \add (example)\add*, undergoing the onesh of Eish Olam\f + \fr 1:7 \ft \xt Isa 66:24; Mt 25:46; Rv 20:10\f*\add (Eternal Fire)\add*. 
\p  
\v 8 Likewise, indeed, these [“certain men,” \xt 1:4\xt*], these dreamers, on the one hand, pollute the basar \add (flesh)\add*; on the other hand, they do not recognize HaMemshalah \add (rule)\add* of glorious heavenly beings; instead, they speak lashon hora with Chillul \nd Hashem\nd* railing against them.  
\v 9 By contrast, Mikha'el the Sar HaMalachim,\f + \fr 1:9 \ft \xt Dan 10:13\f* when he took issue with HaSatan and disputed about the geviyyat Moshe\f + \fr 1:9 \ft Rabbeinu\f*\add (body of Moses)\add*, did not presume to pronounce a slanderous judgment [against HaSatan], but said, “\nd Hashem\nd* rebuke you!”  
\v 10 But, on the one hand, these [men] slander whatever they do not understand; on the other hand, what they do have binah of instinctively, like unreasoning animals, by these things they are destroyed.  
\v 11 Oy to them! Because they walked in the Derech Kayin\f + \fr 1:11 \ft \xt Gn 4:3-8\f* and to the Toyus Bil'am\f + \fr 1:11 \ft \xt Ex 31:16\f*\add (Error of Balaam)\add* they surrendered for revach \add (gain)\add*, and in the mered \add (rebellion)\add* of Korach against HaMemshalah\f + \fr 1:11 \ft \xt Ex 16:1-35\f* they were destroyed!  
\v 12 These [men] are hidden reefs [moored at] your seudas \add (agape-feasts)\add*, feasting with you without yires-hakoved, shepherding themselves, waterless clouds being carried away by winds, autumn trees without fruit, twice dead, torn up from their shorashim \add (roots)\add*,  
\v 13 Wild waves of the sea, foaming up their ma'asim hara'im \add (evil deeds)\add*, wandering kokhavim \add (stars)\add* for whom the shvartz gloom of choshech has been reserved oif eibik \add (forever)\add*. 
\p  
\v 14 But also it was about these [men] that Chanokh, in the seventh [generation] from Adam, prophesied, saying, “Hinei, Adonoi comes with His ten thousands of malachim,  
\v 15 For the purpose of bringing all to Mishpat and for the purpose of proving guilty every neshamah of all of its deeds done without yires-hakoved and of all the harsh things chote'im \add (sinners)\add* without yires-hakoved spoke against Him.”  
\v 16 These [men] are malcontents and fault-finders, walking according to their ta'avot \add (lusts)\add*; their mouth speaks arrogant things, flattering for the tzil \add (purpose)\add* of financial advantage. 
\p  
\v 17 But you, Chaverim, keep in mind the predictions\f + \fr 1:17 \ft \xt 2K 3:3\f* of the Shlichim of Rebbe Melech HaMoshiach Adoneinu Yehoshua,  
\v 18 Because they were telling you that at Acharit HaYamim \add (the End of Days)\add*, there will be leitzim\f + \fr 1:18 \ft \xt Ps 1:1\f*\add (scoffers)\add* walking according to their ta'avot \add (lusts)\add* without yires-hakoved.  
\v 19 These [men] are the ones causing division, worldly men, not having the Ruach Hakodesh.  
\v 20 But you, Chaverim, build yourselves up on what is kodesh kodeshim \add (most holy)\add* of yours, your\f + \fr 1:20 \ft correct, Orthodox Jewish\f* Emunah\f + \fr 1:20 \ft \xt 1:3\ft , the Emunah of the true Dat HaYehudit\f*\add (Faith)\add*, davening in the Ruach Hakodesh.  
\v 21 Keep yourselves in the Ahavas \nd Hashem\nd*, awaiting the rachamim of Rebbe, Melech HaMoshiach Adoneinu Yehoshua unto Chayyei Olam.  
\v 22 To those who are wavering, show rachamim; others, deliver, snatching them out of the Eish.\f + \fr 1:22 \ft Olam, \xt Isa 66:24\f* 
\v 23 On others, have rachamim mixed with yires-hakoved, hating even the undergarment defiled by corrupt human nature. 
\p  
\v 24 Now to the One who is able to stand shomer over you, to make you moineia \add (prevented)\add* from falling, and to set you unblemished in the presence of his Shekhinah, with sasson rav \add (much rejoicing)\add*,  
\v 25 To HaElohim HaYachid Moshieinu \add (to the only G-d our Savior)\add*, through Rebbe Melech HaMoshiach Adoneinu Yehoshua, be HaKavod \add (Glory)\add* and HaGedulah \add (Greatness)\add* and HaMemshalah \add (Rule)\add* and HaGevurah \add (Might)\add* Mei-Olam V'ad Atah V'ad Olemei Olamim \add (before all time, now, and forever.)\add* Omein.